<br>
I bought a handgun a while ago, here in metro-Phoenix.  The process consisted of me walking into Mandell's Shooting Supplies on Scottsdale Road in Scottsdale Arizona (&quot;The West's Most Western Town&quot;), pointing at a Glock 23-C in the glass case, handing the shopkeep my drivers license, filling out a Yes/No form to which I attested that I wasn't currently insane or on drugs -- to which the shopkeep faxed my completed form and my driver's license to the Maricopa County Sherriff's Office.  10 minutes later, the MCSO decided I was &quot;fit&quot; to own a handgun.  I paid cash, walked outside with it, loaded it, put it in a holster, strapped the holster to my hip, and wore it home.<br>
<br>
Obviously, since I've taken part in the process a couple times since then, I don't take any issue with it; but you have to admit, it is a pretty painless process.<br>
<br>
